00:49.200 --> 00:50.200
lucas!

00:51.500 --> 00:52.100
lucas

00:53.300 --> 00:54.900
somebody help!

00:58.800 --> 01:00.300
i don't know. i just
saw him lying by his car.

01:00.335 --> 01:01.900
so tell me again what happened,ma'am.

01:19.500 --> 01:20.300
hello?

01:21.700 --> 01:23.400
yes. this is melinda gordon.

01:25.300 --> 01:27.200
sure i remember you.

01:29.600 --> 01:32.700
lucas? i'm so sorry.

01:33.200 --> 01:36.200
um,yeah,ok.

01:39.500 --> 01:40.400
thanks.

01:41.600 --> 01:42.950
ok. weird.

01:42.985 --> 01:44.300
what was that?

01:45.000 --> 01:46.600
well,this guy from my high school,

01:46.635 --> 01:48.800
lucas marston, he died.

01:50.100 --> 01:51.500
i never heard you talk about him.

01:51.535 --> 01:53.400
was he a good friend? no.

01:53.435 --> 01:54.400
not at all.

01:56.700 --> 01:59.100
so why did i just get
invited to his funeral?

02:03.800 --> 02:06.300
grace: there's haylie.

02:06.400 --> 02:08.699
haylie,hi.

02:12.100 --> 02:13.200
guest of honor here yet?

02:13.300 --> 02:15.300
i don't see him,but
i've seen a couple people

02:15.335 --> 02:17.700
checking me out just in case i did.

02:17.800 --> 02:19.400
honey,i think they were
just checking you out.

02:19.500 --> 02:21.800
i've literally heard,like,5
guys say how beautiful you were.

02:21.900 --> 02:24.700
yeah. meaning how much i've changed,

02:24.735 --> 02:26.400
but one thing has not.

02:26.500 --> 02:27.865
hey. i think they probably included you

02:27.900 --> 02:30.400
because they remembered you
and maybe they liked you.

02:30.500 --> 02:31.700
i was the kid who was caught talking

02:31.800 --> 02:32.900
to dead people,ok?

02:33.000 --> 02:34.600
they called me a freak,a mental case,

02:34.700 --> 02:37.100
and my personal favorite
- meloony gordon.

02:37.200 --> 02:39.300
catchy,i know, but not at the time.

02:39.400 --> 02:40.550
all right. so it was a drag,

02:40.585 --> 02:41.700
but then why are we here?

02:41.800 --> 02:42.800
well,because lucas always
seemed like a nice guy

02:42.900 --> 02:44.500
and grace,too, but then again,

02:44.600 --> 02:46.000
maybe they were so into each other,

02:46.100 --> 02:47.800
they were too busy to be mean.

02:47.835 --> 02:48.865
which one's grace?

02:48.900 --> 02:50.000
uh,pretty blond. the one that got

02:50.100 --> 02:51.500
icy reception from haylie.

02:51.600 --> 02:53.165
they used to be friends.

02:53.200 --> 02:55.300
haylie,you know, she was lucas'

02:55.400 --> 02:57.300
on-and-off-again
girlfriend.

02:57.400 --> 02:58.600
i thought you said you
didn't know these people.

02:58.700 --> 03:01.100
oh,i knew of them. everyone did.

03:01.135 --> 03:03.500
you know,they were a power clique,

03:03.600 --> 03:06.900
superbeautiful and all best friends.

03:06.935 --> 03:08.965
go. let's go.

03:09.000 --> 03:10.600
grace: i'll be right back.

03:10.700 --> 03:14.100
oh. looks like grace is with ryan now.

03:14.200 --> 03:15.365
him i know.

03:15.400 --> 03:16.600
really? how do you know him?

03:16.700 --> 03:20.100
he's a surgical resident
at grandview hospital.

03:20.200 --> 03:21.965
that is so disappointing

03:22.000 --> 03:24.500
when the person who's voted most
likely to succeed actually does.

03:24.600 --> 03:25.700
um... guess i was right

03:25.800 --> 03:27.500
about why i was asked here.

03:27.600 --> 03:28.600
melinda.

03:28.700 --> 03:30.800
grace,hi.

03:30.900 --> 03:33.000
uh,you met my husband jim,right?

03:33.100 --> 03:35.800
yes,hi. and actually, i
have a favor to ask hi.

03:35.900 --> 03:37.165
that i hope you won't mind,

03:37.200 --> 03:39.700
but,um,if you're going
back to grandview,

03:39.800 --> 03:42.400
would you mind riding with me?

03:47.700 --> 03:49.100
grace: the reason i called you was,

03:49.200 --> 03:50.265
you remember in high school

03:50.300 --> 03:53.600
how you said you could see ghosts?

03:53.635 --> 03:56.100
i never said that.

03:56.200 --> 04:00.865
not if i could help
it, and i still don't.

04:00.900 --> 04:07.200
but do you believe that you
can,um,see them,the dead?

04:10.900 --> 04:12.100
have you seen lucas?

04:12.200 --> 04:15.400
no.

04:15.500 --> 04:21.600
so what is it like when
someone is haunting you?

04:21.635 --> 04:22.967
i mean,are they around all the time,

04:23.002 --> 04:24.300
or do they just kind of come and go?

04:24.400 --> 04:27.000
i mean,what can they do to someone?

04:27.100 --> 04:28.800
you mean,to you.

04:31.200 --> 04:35.800
look. i-i found him,

04:35.900 --> 04:38.500
and there was blood, not just on lucas

04:38.600 --> 04:39.800
from where he'd collapsed

04:39.900 --> 04:42.800
but streaked across his car window.

04:42.835 --> 04:44.700
i know it sounds crazy.

04:46.500 --> 04:47.500
i'm so nervous.

04:47.600 --> 04:48.800
grace?

04:50.100 --> 04:52.700
ahh. oh-oh,god. oh,god.

04:52.800 --> 04:54.250
that is disgusting.

04:54.285 --> 04:55.700
are you all right?

04:55.800 --> 04:56.900
melinda, the medical examiner

04:57.000 --> 04:58.100
said that when they found lucas

04:58.200 --> 04:59.200
he had been dead for hours,

04:59.300 --> 05:01.600
but i saw that blood appear,

05:01.635 --> 05:03.865
and ever since i saw it,

05:03.900 --> 05:06.200
i've felt something around me.

05:06.235 --> 05:07.465
i can't describe it.

05:07.500 --> 05:09.500
i'm not sure you have to.

05:19.000 --> 05:22.400
because-because you know the feeling?

05:22.500 --> 05:24.000
yeah. pretty well.

05:26.900 --> 05:28.800
child,whispering: can you see us?

