05:56.100 --> 05:57.560
eli: wait. so the ghost
smeared its own blood

05:57.570 --> 05:58.580
for grace to see?

05:58.700 --> 05:59.860
melinda: well,yeah,eli.

06:00.100 --> 06:01.800
i mean,you've seen them
move objects around.

06:01.900 --> 06:03.800
it's pretty much the same principle.

06:03.900 --> 06:06.000
the on the way home hurled
itself against the windshield?

06:06.100 --> 06:07.700
ghosts can sometimes act out.

06:07.800 --> 06:09.000
hey. if i'm gonna hear ghosts,

06:09.100 --> 06:10.800
i might as well get the whole picture.

06:10.835 --> 06:12.000
you know what? that surprises me

06:12.100 --> 06:14.100
because most people in
your position,they just-

06:14.200 --> 06:16.000
you mean,who died and come
back with bonus features?

06:16.035 --> 06:17.700
you know that many of us?

06:17.800 --> 06:20.165
melinda,i've written books
upon books on subjects

06:20.200 --> 06:23.600
about a thousandth as cool as what's
going on in my skull right now.

06:23.635 --> 06:24.700
i mean, don't get me wrong.

06:24.800 --> 06:26.265
this whole ghost thing,

06:26.300 --> 06:28.165
it's kind of creepy at times,

06:28.200 --> 06:31.600
but this,this psycho paranormal whatever

06:31.700 --> 06:33.100
is a trip.

06:33.200 --> 06:34.300
glad to hear it.

06:34.400 --> 06:35.465
how can i help?

06:35.500 --> 06:37.800
well,anytime that a ghost comes to you-

06:37.835 --> 06:38.917
no. i mean,you.

06:38.952 --> 06:40.000
loop me in.

06:40.100 --> 06:41.200
how else am i gonna learn?

06:41.300 --> 06:42.400
can i use your computer?

06:42.500 --> 06:44.350
eli: who knew hamilton high was

06:44.385 --> 06:46.165
a feeder school for the ivies?

06:46.200 --> 06:48.500
after yale, mr. lucas marston worked

06:48.535 --> 06:50.117
in the skiing industry.

06:50.152 --> 06:51.700
he was a lift attendant.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.200
he dabbled in real estate development.

06:53.300 --> 06:54.800
his dad owns an apartment building.

06:54.900 --> 06:56.000
i overheard someone at the wake saying

06:56.035 --> 06:57.565
that he was the handyman.

06:57.600 --> 06:59.000
so if you know so much about the ghost,

06:59.100 --> 07:00.800
why are we bothering
with the obituary spin?

07:00.900 --> 07:03.600
well,because lucas' background
is just a starting place.

07:03.700 --> 07:05.900
i mean,the truth is,i didn't
get a good look at the ghost.

07:06.000 --> 07:09.300
that alone can tell you something.

07:09.400 --> 07:11.300
chockfull of antioxidants.

07:11.335 --> 07:13.600
no,thanks.

07:13.700 --> 07:16.100
so you think the ghost

07:16.200 --> 07:18.500
miss popular mowed down the
night of her friend's wake

07:18.535 --> 07:19.700
was somebody random?

07:19.800 --> 07:20.965
no. there's always a connection,

07:21.000 --> 07:22.200
but if the ghost that i saw on the road

07:22.300 --> 07:25.200
was lucas,why wasn't
he at his own funeral?

07:25.235 --> 07:26.900
soaking up the kind words.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.300
yeah. something like that.

07:28.400 --> 07:29.600
maybe the words people
said under their breaths

07:29.700 --> 07:30.965
weren't so kind.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.800
call me crazy,but when a
perfectly healthy,bright,

07:33.900 --> 07:36.900
but underachieving 29-year-old
suddenly keels over,

07:36.935 --> 07:37.900
i smell...

07:38.000 --> 07:39.165
drugs.

07:39.200 --> 07:40.700
i haven't seen the
result of the tox report,

07:40.800 --> 07:44.400
but they're saying it was an overdose.

07:44.500 --> 07:46.500
grace,don't do this.

07:46.600 --> 07:47.900
we don't have anything
to feel guilty about.

07:47.935 --> 07:49.565
we know what we did.

07:49.600 --> 07:51.800
i have to scrub up, but we'll talk.

07:51.900 --> 07:54.600
no,we won't, not about this.

08:32.200 --> 08:33.700
more light,please.

08:36.799 --> 08:39.200
would somebody get that
out of my eyes,please?

08:39.299 --> 08:41.400
are you ok, dr. hellar?

08:41.434 --> 08:43.465
yeah.

08:43.500 --> 08:45.300
then why don't you close up?

08:45.335 --> 08:46.500
right.

08:46.600 --> 08:48.700
all right. stitch and dress.

08:56.500 --> 08:59.465
ok.

08:59.500 --> 09:01.900
we're good here.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.600
nice work,everybody.

09:04.900 --> 09:06.000
whoa,whoa. what the hell?

09:06.100 --> 09:08.200
the wound's closed. where's
this blood coming from?

09:08.300 --> 09:10.400
whoa! oh,my god!

09:11.500 --> 09:14.000
no. what's going on?

09:14.100 --> 09:16.900
i'll get dr. dugan.

09:17.000 --> 09:18.400
aah!

09:20.500 --> 09:22.200
i'll take over.

09:29.100 --> 09:30.465
jim,voice-over: ryan
comes tearing out of there.

09:30.500 --> 09:32.800
the nurse i spoke to said
there was blood everywhere.

09:32.900 --> 09:34.400
what happened? i don't know,

09:34.500 --> 09:36.000
but when the surgeon comes back,

09:36.100 --> 09:38.500
no more blood, patient is fine.

09:38.600 --> 09:40.165
the blood has to mean something.

09:40.200 --> 09:43.500
thanks. and why don't you
not go to work right now?

09:43.600 --> 09:45.000
as much as i love
playing hooky with you,

09:45.035 --> 09:46.100
i have to go.

09:46.200 --> 09:48.200
oh. you forgot one of your tear sheets.

09:48.300 --> 09:50.200
wait a minute. we're
putting a 6-burner stove

09:50.300 --> 09:51.100
in the nursery?

09:51.200 --> 09:52.365
it's for the garage.

09:52.400 --> 09:53.700
i was thinking that we could convert it

09:53.800 --> 09:54.800
into a guest house, you know,

09:54.900 --> 09:57.000
for a live-in sitter
or for our mothers.

09:57.035 --> 09:58.165
i mean,it's a good idea,

09:58.200 --> 10:00.665
but,uh,i mean,
converting the garage now.

10:00.700 --> 10:03.000
aren't we getting a
little ahead of ourselves?

10:03.035 --> 10:05.317
because i'm not getting pregnant?

10:05.352 --> 10:07.600
hey. no,no. because when you do,

10:07.700 --> 10:08.900
we'll still have 9 months.

10:09.000 --> 10:11.300
i mean,let me run the
numbers a little bit,

10:11.335 --> 10:12.700
think about it,ok?

10:14.100 --> 10:16.700
ok. sure.

10:20.700 --> 10:25.200
ryan: lucas' death,well,
it freaked us both out,

10:25.300 --> 10:27.000
i have to be honest,

10:27.100 --> 10:28.100
but what happened at the hospital-

10:28.200 --> 10:30.100
i think it was a ghost.

10:33.800 --> 10:35.900
did you feel anything strange,

10:36.000 --> 10:37.100
a chill you couldn't explain,

10:37.135 --> 10:38.400
after lucas died?

10:38.500 --> 10:41.300
ghosts. we're talking ghosts now with-

10:41.335 --> 10:43.617
ryan,i asked melinda for her help.

10:43.652 --> 10:45.900
look. a suture must have ruptured.

10:46.000 --> 10:48.100
i made a mistake,ok? it happens.

10:48.200 --> 10:50.850
i've been stressed.

10:50.885 --> 10:53.500
i work crazy hours,

10:53.600 --> 10:56.300
and my best friend from
high school just died.

10:56.400 --> 10:58.900
so you and lucas were still close?

10:59.000 --> 11:02.100
we were fine.

11:02.200 --> 11:05.300
i am happy to finish my coffee

11:05.400 --> 11:07.065
and go back to my life

11:07.100 --> 11:09.400
because i am not afraid of the d dead,

11:09.500 --> 11:13.700
but you came to me,and an
innocent person lost a lot of blood

11:13.800 --> 11:15.600
because you have something
you need to resolve

11:15.635 --> 11:17.400
with either lucas or someone else.

11:17.435 --> 11:18.600
who else would it be then?

11:18.700 --> 11:21.400
i haven't seen the ghost,
so i don't know who it is,

11:21.435 --> 11:23.100
but when a ghost doesn't
reveal themselves,

11:23.200 --> 11:24.265
it's for a reason.

11:24.300 --> 11:25.800
either they're hiding something,

11:25.835 --> 11:27.300
or they have a project in mind,

11:27.400 --> 11:29.200
like torturing you.

11:31.400 --> 11:32.500
why don't you try to not say that

11:32.600 --> 11:33.400
like you enjoy it?

11:33.500 --> 11:35.000
i don't,

11:35.100 --> 11:38.000
and i don't like seeing souls linger,

11:38.100 --> 11:39.800
but that's what they do when they're

11:39.900 --> 11:41.100
trying to finish something.

11:41.200 --> 11:44.000
well,you're casting an
awfully wide net there.

11:44.100 --> 11:45.700
i don't know what lucas
did for the last 10 years

11:45.800 --> 11:48.300
when he was supposed to be
building a career,a life.

11:48.335 --> 11:50.065
you want to know? ask haylie.

11:50.100 --> 11:52.300
she waited around long enough
for him to get his act together.

11:52.400 --> 11:54.600
all i know is that he o.d.ed at 29,

11:54.700 --> 11:57.000
so if you want to know
what he didn't finish,

11:57.100 --> 11:59.000
why don't you try everything?

12:02.100 --> 12:04.100
and he's got no one
to blame but himself.

12:04.200 --> 12:05.700
oh,my god!

12:08.800 --> 12:10.100
you're bleeding.

12:16.500 --> 12:17.700
ryan.

12:17.800 --> 12:19.000
i need another napkin.

12:23.100 --> 12:24.700
what was that?

12:27.000 --> 12:29.500
you found him. you were
there when the police came.

12:29.600 --> 12:32.200
are they sure his body wasn't moved?

12:32.235 --> 12:33.417
what are you talking about?

12:33.452 --> 12:34.600
grace,let's go. come on.

12:34.700 --> 12:36.200
i've had enough.

12:36.235 --> 12:38.200
ok.

12:38.300 --> 12:40.100
we don't need your
particular brand of help,ok?

12:40.200 --> 12:42.500
i wouldn't be so sure about that.

12:56.800 --> 12:59.500
ah. hamilton high, 1998-

12:59.600 --> 13:01.200
big hair and big dreams.

13:01.300 --> 13:03.265
oh,wait. that's not you!

13:03.300 --> 13:06.500
no,it's not,but will show you lucas.

13:06.600 --> 13:08.765
the guy who died? he's so cute.

13:08.800 --> 13:12.100
yeah. died or was
murdered by his friend.

13:12.135 --> 13:13.200
i saw it in a vision,

13:13.300 --> 13:14.300
but i only got a piece of the story.

13:14.400 --> 13:16.400
ich is not exactly the
story ryan's telling?

13:16.500 --> 13:18.365
no. he seems pretty keen

13:18.400 --> 13:19.900
on blaming lucas for his own death.

13:20.000 --> 13:21.300
he said he was a real screw-up

13:21.335 --> 13:23.817
and that if i doubted him

13:23.852 --> 13:26.076
i could talk to haylie.

13:26.111 --> 13:27.705
well,color me doubtful.

13:27.740 --> 13:29.300
hmm. my favorite color.

13:29.335 --> 13:31.700
ha ha ha!

13:31.800 --> 13:33.300
are you calling haylie?

13:33.400 --> 13:35.300
are you kidding? the girl
was so perfect in high school,

13:35.400 --> 13:36.600
there's not crack in her demeanor.

13:36.700 --> 13:38.400
she would never open up to me.

13:38.500 --> 13:40.500
come on. you are not still afraid

13:40.600 --> 13:42.000
of the popular girl?

13:42.100 --> 13:43.400
hardly.

13:45.500 --> 13:48.900
besides,eli is a very
experienced grief counselor,

13:49.000 --> 13:52.200
and he wants to learn,so
let him melt the ice queen.

13:52.235 --> 13:55.400
i spent a third of my
life as lucas' girlfriend,

13:55.500 --> 13:57.500
give or take our many breakups,

13:57.600 --> 14:01.200
and even in death, who
does he go to? grace.

14:01.300 --> 14:03.400
look,haylie. it isn't just grace.

14:03.500 --> 14:05.100
lucas is haunting ryan,too.

14:05.200 --> 14:06.600
were they rivals?

14:06.700 --> 14:08.100
lucas and grace, i mean,they were

14:08.200 --> 14:10.050
closer to each other than to anybody

14:10.085 --> 14:11.900
they were actually sleeping with.

14:11.935 --> 14:14.465
come on. ryan know this?

14:14.500 --> 14:17.465
well,i'm sure. they never hid it.

14:17.500 --> 14:20.400
they'd be on the phone
for two hours at a stretch.

14:20.500 --> 14:21.865
there was something unhealthy about it.

14:21.900 --> 14:24.000
that wasn't exactly helping
his battle with drugs.

14:24.100 --> 14:25.365
he took antianxiety medication,

14:25.400 --> 14:27.400
but i never saw him take anything else.

14:27.435 --> 14:29.400
i've treated a lot of addicts.

14:29.435 --> 14:33.300
they're very secretive.

14:33.400 --> 14:35.200
he wasn't always.

14:35.300 --> 14:39.500
it wasn't always so
hard for him to be happy.

14:39.600 --> 14:42.200
you make it seem like
something happened.

14:42.235 --> 14:43.517
what was it?

14:43.552 --> 14:44.800
i wish i knew.

14:46.900 --> 14:49.300
i think that ryan and grace do

14:49.400 --> 14:51.900
because senior year, the 3 of them,

14:52.000 --> 14:53.900
they went to look at some colleges.

14:53.935 --> 14:55.400
they were gone for 4 days,

14:55.500 --> 14:59.700
and when they came back,
lucas was never the same.

15:02.200 --> 15:05.800
melinda: haylie gave you
her keys to lucas' apartment?

15:05.900 --> 15:07.165
you're a quick study.

15:07.200 --> 15:09.700
what can i say? people trust me.

15:09.800 --> 15:12.300
i'm a professional.

15:12.400 --> 15:14.200
it sounds like to me that lucas

15:14.300 --> 15:17.400
was still in love with
grace and ryan knew it.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.900
i'm not sure this was about grace.

15:20.000 --> 15:22.200
