31:12.635 --> 31:15.400
we all did.

31:15.500 --> 31:16.400
to lucas.

31:16.500 --> 31:19.600
to lucas! to lucas!

31:19.700 --> 31:20.900
want to do something,

31:21.000 --> 31:22.400
or should i?

31:26.400 --> 31:28.500
we should go outside and talk.

31:28.535 --> 31:30.600
look. i know what grace told you,

31:30.700 --> 31:32.600
and there's a statute of limitations,

31:32.635 --> 31:33.865
even on obsessive guilt.

31:33.900 --> 31:35.000
you might want to restart the clock

31:35.100 --> 31:36.500
from the time that you
prescribed the medicine

31:36.600 --> 31:38.100
that killed your friend.

31:42.100 --> 31:45.400
tell me you didn't give him those drugs.

31:45.500 --> 31:48.265
grace,he came to me,ok?

31:48.300 --> 31:49.500
because he wanted to come clean.

31:49.535 --> 31:50.465
he told you that?

31:50.500 --> 31:52.900
yeah. he brought me up to speed

31:53.000 --> 31:55.100
on the plans that the
two of you made together.

31:55.135 --> 31:57.200
i met with him because he
had inherited some money

31:57.235 --> 31:58.400
and he wanted to put
it into a trust account

31:58.500 --> 32:00.000
for that man's daughter.

32:00.100 --> 32:01.700
he figured he could do some good,

32:01.800 --> 32:02.965
maybe get some peace.

32:03.000 --> 32:05.100
you couldn't let him
have that,could you?

32:05.135 --> 32:06.200
you would rather see him dead.

32:06.235 --> 32:10.900
ah,no.

32:11.000 --> 32:12.500
grace,wait!

32:13.900 --> 32:16.000
you think you're the only
person that cared about him?

32:16.035 --> 32:18.065
he was my best friend.

32:18.100 --> 32:19.400
i was just trying to make things ok.

32:19.500 --> 32:22.065
that's all i ever did.

32:22.100 --> 32:23.500
grace,it was our mistake that

32:23.600 --> 32:25.000
he was driving that car.

32:25.100 --> 32:26.500
it was our fault.

32:26.535 --> 32:27.900
that's the big secret

32:28.000 --> 32:29.400
that we never discuss.

32:29.500 --> 32:31.300
what happened that night,lucas?

32:31.400 --> 32:32.900
i think you know.

32:33.000 --> 32:37.100
you were so responsible,
such a good guy until...

32:37.135 --> 32:38.800
ryan: the party at binghamton.

32:40.300 --> 32:42.000
he's here,isn't he?

32:48.800 --> 32:52.900
since seventh grade,
we were best friends.

32:52.935 --> 32:54.200
on the first day of high school,

32:54.300 --> 32:58.500
he introduced me to the girl
that he'd met over summer,

32:58.600 --> 33:01.300
and every single day,
i fell harder for her.

33:03.400 --> 33:05.600
and nothing happened for so long...

33:05.700 --> 33:07.350
no,man. i'm good,thanks.

33:07.385 --> 33:09.442
until that stupid frat party

33:09.477 --> 33:11.500
at the end of the road trip.

33:25.100 --> 33:26.300
who was that?

33:29.100 --> 33:30.000
here you go,lucas.

33:30.100 --> 33:31.700
thanks,man.

33:33.700 --> 33:36.000
later,i tried to act
like nothing happened,

33:36.100 --> 33:37.865
and i realized that we all were

33:37.900 --> 33:40.600
and that lucas knew and
that's why he was drinking.

33:40.635 --> 33:41.900
it wasn't like him.

33:42.000 --> 33:52.200
it was our fault. we did this to him.

33:52.300 --> 33:54.100
leaving that guy on the road,

33:54.200 --> 33:56.500
i wasn't just protecting myself.

33:56.535 --> 33:59.400
i was protecting all of us,

33:59.500 --> 34:01.400
and when my best friend came to me,

34:01.500 --> 34:04.400
falling apart after 10 years,

34:04.500 --> 34:05.800
i just tried to do the same thing.

34:05.900 --> 34:08.300
i tried to save him...

34:08.400 --> 34:10.900
or at least,that's what
i thought i was doing.

34:10.935 --> 34:13.400
i didn't come asking
for permission this time.

34:13.500 --> 34:17.465
ryan,a man died because i was drinking,

34:17.500 --> 34:20.000
because we left him there like
he was some kind of animal.

34:20.034 --> 34:21.400
ahh,ahh.

34:21.500 --> 34:23.199
because i told you to.

34:23.300 --> 34:24.500
look. the guy was gone.

34:24.600 --> 34:25.800
there was nothing we could do.

34:25.900 --> 34:27.500
he had a wife and a kid.

34:27.600 --> 34:29.665
i can't live like this anymore.

34:29.699 --> 34:31.500
really? how are you gonna
live in a 10x10 cell?

34:31.600 --> 34:35.699
look. as your friend, i am begging you,

34:35.800 --> 34:37.800
please stop torturing yourself.

34:37.835 --> 34:41.100
if i don't do this,

34:41.199 --> 34:43.100
i think i'm gonna die.

34:43.199 --> 34:44.949
i can't get out of my head,

34:44.985 --> 34:46.699
i can't sleep, i can't think.

34:46.800 --> 34:48.500
you still seeing your shrink?

34:48.600 --> 34:51.364
i'm done with all that.

34:51.400 --> 34:54.264
whatever decision you
make,i'm behind you,

34:54.300 --> 34:57.300
but don't make a decision
like this without a clear head.

34:57.400 --> 34:59.700
look. you said you
haven't been sleeping.

34:59.800 --> 35:01.700
i'm gonna give you something,ok? yeah.

35:01.800 --> 35:03.900
you just take a couple of days.

35:06.000 --> 35:07.200
do that for me, all right?

35:07.235 --> 35:08.500
yeah.

35:08.600 --> 35:12.100
i told him don't mix
those pills with anything.

35:12.200 --> 35:13.600
i swear,

35:13.700 --> 35:15.100
and when i found out that he o.d.ed-

35:15.200 --> 35:17.365
ask him. please,melinda.

35:17.400 --> 35:22.400
if lucas is here, ask
him if that is true.

35:22.500 --> 35:24.200
he told me.

35:30.400 --> 35:32.000
but it wasn't the pills.

35:32.100 --> 35:34.400
it was the silence. i remember now.

35:34.435 --> 35:37.200
late at night every night.

35:37.300 --> 35:38.700
i hadn't slept for so long.

35:38.800 --> 35:41.300
the pills my shrink
had prescribed to me,

35:41.400 --> 35:43.100
they weren't helping,
they didn't do anything,

35:43.135 --> 35:46.800
so what harm could a sleeping pill do?

35:46.900 --> 35:48.400
i woke up again.

35:48.500 --> 35:50.500
it had to have been hours
since i took the first one.

35:50.600 --> 35:52.900
why wasn't i sleeping?

36:05.700 --> 36:07.700
i went out to my car to get headphones.

36:07.735 --> 36:09.100
i had neighbors,

36:09.200 --> 36:11.300
and next thing i know...

36:15.100 --> 36:17.500
i'm standing over my own body.

36:17.600 --> 36:20.700
i saw grace. she looked so sad,

36:20.800 --> 36:23.500
even before she found me.

36:23.600 --> 36:25.200
i needed to make them understand.

36:25.300 --> 36:30.600
the sadness,it just doesn't go away.

36:30.700 --> 36:32.265
lucas may not have realized it,

36:32.300 --> 36:34.400
but i think he was trying to save you.

36:34.500 --> 36:35.800
from what?

36:37.200 --> 36:39.900
from making the same mistake he did.

36:40.000 --> 36:41.665
he was afraid that if you kept

36:41.700 --> 36:45.200
your guilt a secret
it would ruin your life

36:45.300 --> 36:47.500
the way that it ruined his.

36:47.600 --> 36:51.065
lucas,i'm sorry.

36:51.100 --> 36:55.700
we are both so sorry.

36:55.800 --> 36:59.700
i didn't see it coming.

36:59.800 --> 37:03.900
my girlfriend, my best friend.

37:08.700 --> 37:12.400
did you? you saw everything
back in high school.

37:12.500 --> 37:14.500
you were always so quiet,

37:14.600 --> 37:17.600
taking it all in.

37:17.700 --> 37:21.400
you're asking me?

37:21.500 --> 37:23.900
what a difference 10 years makes.

37:31.500 --> 37:35.100
what i see now is that
it was an accident-

37:35.135 --> 37:37.700
the crash,your death, all of it.

37:37.800 --> 37:41.000
you made a mistake.

37:41.100 --> 37:42.300
it's time for you to move on

37:42.400 --> 37:45.900
and let your friends do the same.

37:56.800 --> 38:00.400
mrs. graber,these are the
two people i told you about.

38:00.500 --> 38:03.900
this is grace, and this is ryan.

38:07.700 --> 38:09.100
i hope she can forgive them.

38:09.200 --> 38:10.600
they're going to the authorities,

38:10.700 --> 38:12.100
they're taking responsibility.

38:12.135 --> 38:14.700
maybe that will help.

38:14.800 --> 38:17.100
i don't think she wants revenge.

38:17.200 --> 38:19.800
i think she wants to
know what it was like

38:19.900 --> 38:22.365
for her husband

38:22.400 --> 38:24.100
in those final moments.

38:30.400 --> 38:33.500
maybe she'll take comfort
in knowing he wasn't alone.

38:54.300 --> 38:57.500
all those years, you held it in

38:57.600 --> 38:59.900
for grace, for both of them.

39:01.900 --> 39:05.500
it's all i could think about

39:05.535 --> 39:06.800
my whole adult life.

39:06.900 --> 39:10.800
well,now you can just let go.

39:10.900 --> 39:13.500
but what comes next?

39:13.600 --> 39:15.800
the light.

39:15.900 --> 39:17.600
what's that like?

39:17.700 --> 39:19.900
i don't know.

39:20.000 --> 39:23.900
d- doesn't that
s- scare you?

39:24.000 --> 39:25.700
the light doesn't scare me.

39:25.800 --> 39:28.300
no,no,no.

39:28.400 --> 39:30.300
i'm talking about the unknown.

39:30.400 --> 39:32.300
i'm just like anyone else.

39:32.335 --> 39:34.200
of course it scares me.

39:34.300 --> 39:35.200
yeah.

39:35.300 --> 39:38.100
but it's ok to be scared.

39:45.600 --> 39:47.200
wow!

39:55.500 --> 39:59.400
take care of them, will you,all of them?

39:59.500 --> 40:02.000
i will.

40:02.100 --> 40:05.500
you're all right, meloony gordon.

40:05.600 --> 40:07.700
don't let anyone tell you otherwise.

40:37.600 --> 40:40.900
hey.

40:41.000 --> 40:43.000
what are you doing?

40:43.100 --> 40:44.000
i lost your tear sheet,

40:44.100 --> 40:46.300
so i'm kind of winging it right now.

40:46.335 --> 40:48.500
no. i mean,i thought we were gonna wait

40:48.600 --> 40:49.700
until i got pregnant

40:49.800 --> 40:52.400
because then we would
still have 9 months.

40:52.500 --> 40:54.100
yeah. yeah, that was my plan.

40:54.200 --> 40:57.400
very logical, but,uh,didn't seem to

40:57.435 --> 40:59.200
make you very happy.

41:02.600 --> 41:04.000
it's not you.

41:05.100 --> 41:07.765
it's what i do.

41:07.800 --> 41:10.100
silly fears and anxieties,

41:10.200 --> 41:12.700
stupid things that ghosts say.

41:12.800 --> 41:14.100
like what?

41:17.300 --> 41:18.500
what?

41:22.200 --> 41:26.200
that there might be
a price for me to pay

41:26.300 --> 41:30.500
for what i do, putting myself

41:30.600 --> 41:34.400
in places where i might not belong.

41:34.500 --> 41:35.700
what kind of places?

41:35.800 --> 41:38.800
the unknown...

41:38.900 --> 41:40.400
death.

41:42.300 --> 41:46.400
you know,that's exactly why we do this.

41:46.500 --> 41:48.250
yeah. this project, all of it.

41:48.285 --> 41:50.000
i was wrong, you were right.

41:50.035 --> 41:51.000
why?

41:51.100 --> 41:52.100
because of what you do.

41:52.200 --> 41:54.465
every day,you know, you believe.

41:54.500 --> 41:55.700
we should believe that the right thing

41:55.800 --> 41:57.100
is gonna happen no matter what,

41:57.200 --> 41:59.800
so we just keep pushing
and pushing until it does.

42:01.800 --> 42:02.865
what if it doesn't?

42:02.900 --> 42:04.600
well,then we push some more.

42:07.000 --> 42:09.400
where did you learn to be so brave?

42:09.435 --> 42:11.167
where do you think?

42:11.202 --> 42:12.900
she's right here.

